  "28-22": (
    caption: [Stringent response in E. coli. This response to amino acid starvation is triggered by binding of an uncharged tRNA in the ribosomal A site. A protein called stringent factor binds to the ribosome and cata- lyzes the synthesis of pppGpp, which is converted by a phosphohydrolase to ppGpp. The signal ppGpp reduces transcription of some genes and increases that of others, in part by binding to the (cid:3) subunit of RNA poly- merase and altering the enzyme’s promoter specificity. Synthesis of rRNA is reduced when ppGpp levels increase. 28.2 Regulation of Gene Expression in Bacteria 1171],
