    caption: [Regulation of bacterial mRNA function in trans by sRNAs. Several sRNAs (small RNAs)—DsrA, RprA, and OxyS—are involved in regulation of the rpoS gene. All require the protein Hfq, an RNA chaperone that facilitates RNA-RNA pairing. Hfq has a toroid structure, with a pore in the center. (a) DsrA promotes translation by pairing with one strand of a stem-loop structure that otherwise blocks the ribosome-binding site. RprA (not shown) acts in a similar way. (b) OxyS blocks translation by pairing with the ribosome-binding site.],
