    caption: [Distribution of the fushi tarazu (ftz) gene product in ear- ly Drosophila embryos. (a) Following a gene-specific staining procedure, the gene product can be detected in seven bands around the circumfer- ence of the embryo. These bands (b) appear as dark spots (generated by a radioactive label) in a cross-sectional autoradiograph and demarcate the anterior margins of the segments that will appear in the late embryo.],
